# Clerk Authentication

This document outlines guidelines for working with Clerk authentication in the SECInsightAI project.

## Clerk Version Compatibility

This project uses Clerk v6, which has different import patterns than previous versions. Always use the correct imports for v6:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct imports for Clerk v6
import { auth, currentUser, clerkClient } from '@clerk/nextjs';
import { SignIn, SignUp, UserButton } from '@clerk/nextjs';

// ❌ Incorrect/deprecated imports
import { withAuth } from '@clerk/nextjs/server'; // Use middleware instead
```

## Getting User Information

### Server Components and API Routes

```typescript
// In server components or API routes
import { auth, currentUser } from '@clerk/nextjs';

// Get the user ID and session
const { userId, sessionId } = auth();
if (!userId) {
  // Handle unauthenticated user
}

// Get the full user object (in async contexts)
const user = await currentUser();
if (!user) {
  // Handle user not found
}

// Access user properties
const email = user.emailAddresses.find(
  email => email.id === user.primaryEmailAddressId
)?.emailAddress;
```

### Client Components

```typescript
// In client components
'use client';
import { useAuth, useUser } from '@clerk/nextjs';

function MyComponent() {
  const { userId, sessionId, isLoaded, isSignedIn } = useAuth();
  const { user } = useUser();
  
  if (!isLoaded) {
    return <div>Loading...</div>;
  }
  
  if (!isSignedIn) {
    return <div>Please sign in</div>;
  }
  
  return <div>Hello, {user.firstName}</div>;
}
```

## Protecting Routes

Use Clerk middleware to protect routes:

```typescript
// In middleware.ts
import { authMiddleware } from '@clerk/nextjs';

export default authMiddleware({
  publicRoutes: ['/'],
});

export const config = {
  matcher: ['/((?!.+\\.[\\w]+$|_next).*)', '/', '/(api|trpc)(.*)'],
};
```

## Common Issues

### Import Errors

If you see errors like "Module '@clerk/nextjs' has no exported member 'auth'":

1. Check that you're using the correct imports for your Clerk version
2. Make sure @clerk/nextjs is properly installed
3. Try clearing Next.js cache: `rm -rf .next` and restart the dev server

### Webhook Configuration

When setting up the webhook to sync Clerk users with your database:

1. Add the webhook URL in the Clerk dashboard
2. Ensure the `CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET` is set in your environment variables
3. Test the webhook with sample events

